Subject: [PATCH] userguide: document exit confirmation dialog

In the section "Exiting i3", document the confirmation dialog (nagbar)
that will show when the user presses the default keys to exit in such a
way to hint that it is configurable.
---
 docs/userguide | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/docs/userguide b/docs/userguide
index ff46d62..681c19f 100644
--- a/docs/userguide
+++ b/docs/userguide
@@ -153,6 +153,7 @@ to upgrade to a newer version of i3) you can use +$mod+Shift+r+.
 === Exiting i3
 
 To cleanly exit i3 without killing your X server, you can use +$mod+Shift+e+.
+By default, a dialog will ask you to confirm if you really want to quit.
 
 === Floating
 
